description: Visually inspect the internal circuit of the control module for possible wiring errors, misconnection, or swapped cables within the module itself., outcome='All internal inspections of the control module components and wiring were successful, with no observable internal faults or misconnected/swapped cables detected. There are no polarity inversions identified among the labeled cables. The "Inverted Cables Indicator (red)" is lit, but the diagnostic note confirms this is nominal for its wiring configuration.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Cable connections/orientation between modules,
description: Systematically trace the cable runs and fast-connection terminal hookups between all modules, and visually inspect the polarity/orientation of every connection. Look for any swapped pairs or connection configuration errors at the inter-module fast connectors, especially at interface points., outcome='All cable polarity and orientation inspections were completed successfully. No polarity inversions were detected at any module or fast-connection interface. All (+) cables are connected to corresponding (+) ports, and all (−) cables to (−) ports throughout the PSU, Control, and Load modules.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=110.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Polarity labels at cable exits/entries on modules,
description: Verify and physically confirm the polarity labeling inside each module, especially at the points where cables exit the power supply, control module, and load module. Ensure that labeling inside the cubes actually corresponds to what is marked as (+) and (−) at the connectors (sometimes internal wiring may be mislabeled or swapped)., outcome='All observed cables are correctly labeled as (+) and (−) at each segment, with no internal faults detected. The internal port status corresponds to either "connected" or "hidden" as appropriate for each module. No polarity inversion was detected during your inspection.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
